No country is named but a source with knowledge of the inquiry said it was focused on the United Arab Emirates (UAE). The UAE did not comment when approached by the BBC. July's attack killed 53 migrants and injured 130, and was described as a potential war crime by a United Nations official. Most of those killed at the Tajoura migrant detention centre, east of the capital, Tripoli, are believed to have been sub-Saharan Africans attempting to reach Europe from Libya. --BBC--